courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to:

1. Understand how to design an AI system for a specific task, including data preparation, model selection, model training, and model deployment;
2. Develop the programming skills for vector operations and construction of different network structures, including multi-layer perceptron, convolutional neural networks, and recurrent neural networks;
3. Develop the programming skills for data preparation, data loading, parallelism and optimization, parallel training, and distributed training;
4. Develop the system design skills to build an AI project, including housing price prediction, visual classification, and text analysis;
5. Design an AI application using the pretrained large foundational models, including stable diffusion-based image generation, large language models, and image segmentation.
